UPDATE (March 26): A Washington, D.C., federal court has released a new order that puts the trans military ban back in motion.
This ban will impact over 13,700 soldiers in the United States military.
This is developing news...***A federal judge has thrown a wrench into the Trump administration’s plan to implement its ban on transgender people in the military, saying her injunction against the ban still stands.
But lawyers representing the transgender troops and others challenging the ban contended that Kollar-Kotelly’s injunction was still valid.